The Dean being in Ireland sent Mrs Howerd a piece of Indian Plad made in that Kingdom; which ye Queen seeing took from her & wore it herself, & sent to ye Dean for as much as wou'd cloath herself & Children; desiring he wou'd send ye charge of it. He did the former, it cost thirty five pounds, but he said he wou'd have nothing except ye Medals. He went next Summer to Engd; was treated as usual, & she being then Queen, ye Dean was promis'd a settlement in Engd:, but return'd as he went, & instead of favour or Medals, hath been ever since under her Majesty's displeasure····· ···· the Medals were ·······
